IFCInstanceComp.Description: Returns a token we can use to execute additional web service calls.
IFCInstanceComp.Name: Call Magento Login WS

ElementsComp.elementdescription: Get started here. Open the Debugger using Ctrl+7 or click the yellow bug icon. Set Breakpoints. Click the Run icon. This will activate the web service flow above and the directory scanner. Either can be used but I find the web service easier.

Choose a flow to execute. Create Order is a good one to start. See google docs for what needs to happen in Magento for this work: https://docs.google.com/document/d/139FiJgBSO_fpyZtbY43Vlirr_u_DzBM9sqjXdvr9Y4g/edit#

C.OrderIncrementId
C.UserString is used by the directory scanner. We pull the filename as the order id using this formula: StrToken(Flip(StrToken(Flip(Trim( C.UserString )),1,'\')),1,'.')

C.OrderIncrementId
If the Create Order trigger is used, we pull the order number like this: Str( F.Magento_Order_Number ,'10')
